  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rural WASH Information Management Systems SMS Notification and Response (RWIMS.SNR)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will be aimed at building capacity in RWIMS.SNR,  a mobile phone-to-internet based information and response system technology at national, provincial, district and community levels in 9 districts in Mashonaland East for improved utilisation of data for timely reporting, planning and decision making and improved response to WASH breakdowns by service providers. the project will also ensure sustainability of this system through supporting district and ward levels to develop and institutionalise RWIMS.SNR sustainability plans. These project activities will result in improved access to safe drinking water, adequate sanitation, and good hygiene practices in Mashonaland East Province through strengthened planning and monitoring of WASH services.</narrative>
  </description>
